WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:04.221
[Indistinct conversations,
distorted voices]

00:04.265 --> 00:06.136
♪ I wanna know

00:06.180 --> 00:08.356
[Voices echoing]

00:08.399 --> 00:11.881
♪ What you're thinking

00:13.100 --> 00:17.930
♪ There are some things
you can't hide ♪

00:17.974 --> 00:19.584
♪ I wanna know

00:19.628 --> 00:22.674
♪ What you're thinking

00:22.718 --> 00:24.850
♪ There are some things...

00:24.894 --> 00:27.984
[Music slowing,
voice distorting]

00:28.028 --> 00:31.248
[Crowd screaming,
voices echoing]

00:34.643 --> 00:36.949
[Breathing heavily]

00:36.993 --> 00:39.126
[Bird cawing in distance]

00:44.609 --> 00:46.655
[Down-tempo music plays]

01:23.126 --> 01:32.135
♪

01:32.179 --> 01:34.659
[Watch ticking]

01:34.703 --> 01:36.705
♪

01:36.748 --> 01:39.229
[Walkers growling]

02:30.672 --> 02:39.246
♪

02:39.289 --> 02:41.509
[Birds chirping]

02:41.552 --> 02:44.164
[Engine revving]

02:44.207 --> 02:45.600
[Man whistles]

02:45.643 --> 02:50.082
♪

02:50.126 --> 02:51.954
[Engine idling]

02:51.997 --> 02:53.869
Felix:
I know.

02:53.912 --> 02:56.828
You're blown away
by my awesome buzz cut.

02:56.872 --> 02:58.003
Did it myself.

02:58.047 --> 03:00.484
Jackass.

03:06.360 --> 03:12.279
♪

03:14.542 --> 03:17.240
Thank you.

03:17.284 --> 03:19.851
[Down-tempo music plays]

03:19.895 --> 03:25.770
♪

03:25.814 --> 03:28.512
Iris: Interesting collection.
Very eclectic.

03:28.556 --> 03:33.169
What can I say?
Uh...I'm a renaissance man.

03:33.213 --> 03:34.518
Hm.

03:34.562 --> 03:36.694
Well, if you need someone
to read them to,

03:36.738 --> 03:38.305
I'm totally here for you.

03:38.348 --> 03:40.437
[Exhales sharply]

03:45.573 --> 03:50.665
♪

03:50.708 --> 03:51.927
Yo.

03:53.145 --> 03:56.279
No way.
Thirteen and a half?

03:56.323 --> 03:58.281
Hey, if the shoe fits...

03:58.325 --> 04:05.332
♪

04:05.375 --> 04:07.856
Unbelievable.

04:07.899 --> 04:10.337
Really.I mean, you are a wizard.

04:10.380 --> 04:11.947
Please, teach me
another one.

04:11.990 --> 04:17.213
Master that trick first,
and then -- and only then...

04:17.257 --> 04:20.042
will I show you more.

04:21.870 --> 04:26.527
I mean, entertainment like thishas just not been available.

04:36.058 --> 04:46.547
♪

04:46.590 --> 04:50.202
I got somethingfor you to wash that down with.

04:50.246 --> 04:52.770
Had it chillingout back in the stream.

04:52.814 --> 04:55.164
[Plastic crinkling]

04:55.773 --> 04:57.819
[Chuckles]

04:57.862 --> 05:01.170
Is this legit?
Mountain Dew?

05:01.213 --> 05:02.824
[Chuckles]

05:02.867 --> 05:06.044
Good as new behind some crates
in an old gas station.

05:06.088 --> 05:08.525
I will never stop
missing these.

05:08.569 --> 05:11.528
I mean, I used to drink thislike water back in the day.

05:11.572 --> 05:12.747
Mm.

05:13.400 --> 05:15.924
Whoo!
[Exhales deeply]

05:16.794 --> 05:17.708
Mmm!

05:17.752 --> 05:19.884
Shit!
Yeah.

05:21.408 --> 05:23.540
What else did you findout there, huh?

05:23.584 --> 05:25.281
Besides that bling.

05:25.325 --> 05:27.370
Big cluster moving south.

05:27.414 --> 05:30.330
Lots of blocked roads
along the main route.

05:30.373 --> 05:33.333
As long as we keep to the side
streets, we should be good.

05:33.376 --> 05:35.770
How about what <i>you</i>found?

05:35.813 --> 05:38.816
Couple con men
and a stolen CRM truck.

05:38.860 --> 05:41.123
Mm, they're all right.

05:41.166 --> 05:42.646
And plus, we got that truck,

05:42.690 --> 05:45.432
and it'll get us to New Yorkin days instead of weeks.

05:45.475 --> 05:47.216
There's not enough fuel
to get us to New York.

05:47.259 --> 05:48.391
You know that, right?

05:48.435 --> 05:49.871
Well, Tony,
the older one,

05:49.914 --> 05:52.090
he's got a leadon where we can get some more.

05:52.134 --> 05:53.483
Tony:
Ladies and gentlemen,

05:53.527 --> 05:56.573
I present to youone Civic Republic military map.

05:56.617 --> 05:57.879
[Claps hands]
As you can see,

05:57.922 --> 05:59.402
there are no landmarks
designated,

05:59.446 --> 06:01.404
no points of interest labeled.

06:01.448 --> 06:06.235
To all appearances,
this looks to be useless.

06:06.278 --> 06:09.456
However...
looks can be deceiving.

06:10.718 --> 06:12.763
When Percy discovered these
in the truck,

06:12.807 --> 06:14.939
they took me back
to the colored lenses I used

06:14.983 --> 06:18.421
in my infamous Prism of Light
illusion.

06:18.465 --> 06:20.641
Just set them up
at the proper distances,

06:20.684 --> 06:24.079
shine a powerful-enough beam
of light through them, and...

06:24.122 --> 06:25.341
presto!

06:25.385 --> 06:27.865
[Down-tempo music plays]

06:27.909 --> 06:30.172
♪

06:30.215 --> 06:33.871
See those little oil drops
scattered around?

06:33.915 --> 06:40.661
Hidden CRM fuel caches
and all the gas we need.

06:40.704 --> 06:42.358
The ones we've hit so far

06:42.402 --> 06:44.882
have mostly been shacks
with, uh, landing pads --

06:44.926 --> 06:47.102
all unmanned
and unguarded.

06:47.145 --> 06:49.060
Helicopters touch down,
they refuel,

06:49.104 --> 06:50.453
and they take off again.

06:50.497 --> 06:53.195
I, uh, can't believe it.

06:53.238 --> 07:03.161
♪

07:03.205 --> 07:05.642
[Footsteps approaching]

07:12.780 --> 07:19.874
♪

07:19.917 --> 07:23.660
You know,
grifting's kind of <i>my</i>thing.

07:23.704 --> 07:25.314
[Clears throat]

07:25.357 --> 07:27.577
Uh, I just needed to borrow themfor a minute.

07:27.621 --> 07:29.013
I would have asked,

07:29.057 --> 07:30.754
but I didn't want to makea big deal out of it.

07:30.798 --> 07:32.103
It's probably nothing.

07:32.147 --> 07:34.454
Yeah.
What's probably nothing?

07:35.629 --> 07:36.717
[Clears throat]

07:36.760 --> 07:38.849
How'd you get
one of their maps?

07:38.893 --> 07:42.070
I'll explain later.

07:42.113 --> 07:44.115
Hold this.

07:44.159 --> 07:49.120
♪

07:49.164 --> 07:50.687
Tony:
Okay.

07:50.731 --> 07:52.863
Where are we
dropping you off?

07:55.170 --> 07:56.301
Um...

07:56.998 --> 07:59.827
Honestly, we don't --
we don't know yet.

07:59.870 --> 08:02.133
What do you mean
you don't know yet?

08:02.177 --> 08:05.093
[Inhales deeply]
Listen.

08:05.136 --> 08:06.964
I'm gonna be straight with you,
all right?

08:07.008 --> 08:10.185
The girls' father is at aCivic Republic research facility

08:10.228 --> 08:12.448
somewhere in New York.

08:12.492 --> 08:14.232
If the CR knew

08:14.276 --> 08:16.931
we were even <i>trying</i>to find
one of their facilities,

08:16.974 --> 08:18.367
we could all be in danger.

08:18.410 --> 08:19.934
If Percy and I were averseto danger,

08:19.977 --> 08:22.023
we wouldn't be driving aroundin one of their trucks.

08:22.066 --> 08:23.851
But if you don't even knowwhere you're going,

08:23.894 --> 08:25.548
how is this arrangement of oursgonna work?

08:25.592 --> 08:28.333
We'll figure it out, make it
work with the intel we got.

08:28.377 --> 08:32.947
If that means flying blind
till we do, then we fly blind.

08:35.036 --> 08:37.299
Crowd:
[Chanting] Mallick! Mallick!

08:37.342 --> 08:39.649
Mallick! Mallick!
Mallick!

08:39.693 --> 08:41.216
All right, all right.Shut up.

08:41.259 --> 08:43.566
Mallick! Mallick!
Mallick!

08:43.610 --> 08:45.612
How about a targetand trajectory report

08:45.655 --> 08:47.396
from my designated spotter?

08:47.439 --> 08:51.226
Final target is approximately
1.4 meters due south

08:51.269 --> 08:52.967
of our current position.

08:53.010 --> 08:55.186
Also, I feel it's my duty
to inform you

08:55.230 --> 08:57.188
of some change
in wind conditions.

08:57.232 --> 08:59.843
Private First Class Owens
just ripped a beer fart

08:59.887 --> 09:01.715
from the east.

09:01.758 --> 09:03.455
Now...

09:03.499 --> 09:05.936
<i>["What's on Your Mind"</i>playing
on jukebox]

09:05.980 --> 09:08.678
[Crowd chanting softly]...fire.

09:10.462 --> 09:11.768
Fire.

09:11.812 --> 09:12.987
Crowd:
...Mallick...

09:13.030 --> 09:15.685
[Cheering]

09:15.729 --> 09:21.082
♪

09:21.125 --> 09:22.692
♪ I find myself...

09:22.736 --> 09:25.608
♪ Didn't I treat you right,
now? ♪

09:25.652 --> 09:28.916
♪ Didn't I?

09:28.959 --> 09:32.397
♪ Didn't I do
the best I could? ♪

09:32.441 --> 09:35.444
♪ Didn't I?

09:35.487 --> 09:38.752
♪ Didn't I give you
everything? ♪

09:38.795 --> 09:41.711
♪ Didn't I?

09:41.755 --> 09:43.191
♪ I tried my best
just to be a man ♪

09:43.234 --> 09:45.585
Ah.
[Chuckles]

09:45.628 --> 09:47.630
That still hurt?

09:47.674 --> 09:49.197
Only when I laugh.

09:49.240 --> 09:50.198
[Chuckles]

09:50.241 --> 09:53.157
♪ Didn't I do it, baby?

09:53.201 --> 09:55.769
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

09:55.812 --> 09:59.686
That morning...
in the Devil's Pass --

09:59.729 --> 10:01.078
You ever think about that?

10:01.122 --> 10:03.080
You ever <i>stop</i>thinking
about it?

10:03.124 --> 10:06.997
♪ Why you wanna leave me,
baby? ♪

10:07.041 --> 10:09.304
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

10:09.347 --> 10:13.047
♪ Didn't I treat you right?

10:13.090 --> 10:14.744
♪

10:14.788 --> 10:19.140
Well, the only thing you need toremember about that morning...

10:19.183 --> 10:21.098
is I had your back
and you had mine.

10:21.142 --> 10:22.578
♪

10:22.622 --> 10:25.059
♪ That a woman could --

10:25.102 --> 10:27.757
Woman on television:
This is a WVPQ special report.

10:27.801 --> 10:29.846
Man on television:
This evening we are following

10:29.890 --> 10:31.935
a tense situation
outside Garnet Medical Center,

10:31.979 --> 10:34.764
which is now the sixth local
hospital to go into lockdown

10:34.808 --> 10:37.637
and close its doors to new
patients in the last 24 hours.

10:37.680 --> 10:39.682
As with the others,
we're receiving reports

10:39.726 --> 10:41.684
of chaos and confusion...

10:41.728 --> 10:44.513
[Voice fades]

10:47.647 --> 10:49.344
Percy:
Anything?

10:51.172 --> 10:52.260
Yeah.

10:52.303 --> 10:53.304
Hey.

10:53.348 --> 10:55.350
You see that?

10:55.393 --> 10:57.439
[Down-tempo music plays]

10:57.482 --> 10:59.571
Get Hope.

10:59.615 --> 11:07.144
♪

11:07.188 --> 11:09.712
This is the map
Lieutenant Colonel Kublek

11:09.756 --> 11:12.497
gave me and Hope
before we left the university.

11:12.541 --> 11:14.369
Some of the markings
on the overlays

11:14.412 --> 11:16.458
didn't form symbols
on the other map.

11:16.501 --> 11:19.635
But when we tried it
on this one...

11:19.679 --> 11:25.032
♪

11:25.075 --> 11:27.774
And there it is.

11:28.992 --> 11:31.342
It's a double helix.
It's a DNA strand.

11:31.386 --> 11:32.735
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

11:32.779 --> 11:34.737
Are you saying that you thinkthis is --

11:34.781 --> 11:35.956
What else could it be?

11:35.999 --> 11:37.958
I think we know where Dad is.

11:44.312 --> 11:50.622
♪

11:53.800 --> 11:55.976
Ithaca.

11:56.019 --> 11:57.368
Ithaca, New York.

11:57.412 --> 11:59.370
That's your finish line?Yeah.

11:59.414 --> 12:02.156
[Laughter in distance]

12:02.199 --> 12:05.986
Hm. Nice to see Percy spending
time with kids his own age.

12:06.029 --> 12:07.204
I bet.

12:07.248 --> 12:08.815
I mean,I did see him go upstairs

12:08.858 --> 12:11.078
with a bottle of his booze,
so...

12:11.121 --> 12:12.906
I don't know.Maybe I should go check on them.

12:12.949 --> 12:14.777
Or you could let them
be teenagers.

12:14.821 --> 12:16.474
They deserve
a little celebration.

12:16.518 --> 12:19.086
So do you, my friend,
after the exciting discovery.

12:19.129 --> 12:22.742
He's right.
You do.

12:22.785 --> 12:24.787
Perimeter check.
I'll be back.

12:24.831 --> 12:27.442
Hey.
You good?

12:27.485 --> 12:29.836
Yeah.
I'm just tired is all.

12:29.879 --> 12:31.881
[Down-tempo music plays]

12:31.925 --> 12:37.626
♪

12:37.669 --> 12:41.412
Took out an empty this morning.
He was wearing the EGA.

12:41.456 --> 12:42.805
Uh-huh.

12:42.849 --> 12:46.287
Brought back some memories --
good and bad.

12:46.330 --> 12:47.854
He was a Marine.

12:47.897 --> 12:49.769
He still is.

12:49.812 --> 12:51.814
So am I.

12:51.858 --> 12:56.471
♪

12:56.514 --> 12:57.864
Ooh.

12:57.907 --> 12:58.908
Ooh?

12:58.952 --> 12:59.866
Oh!

12:59.909 --> 13:01.432
[Laughing]
Oh!

13:01.476 --> 13:04.958
Why should they be having
all the fun, huh?

13:05.001 --> 13:06.873
All right.

13:06.916 --> 13:09.789
[Mid-tempo music playing
in distance]

13:09.832 --> 13:13.053
♪

13:13.096 --> 13:15.272
Elton, try that out.

13:15.316 --> 13:17.057
Okay.

13:17.100 --> 13:18.406
Wait.
Just, like...

13:18.449 --> 13:19.711
Silas.

13:19.755 --> 13:21.148
I'm good. Thanks.Hope: All right.

13:21.191 --> 13:23.454
♪ A feeling I've never felt

13:23.498 --> 13:26.196
[Grunts]
Interesting.

13:26.240 --> 13:30.113
It's like a warm stack of nailsare hugging my insides.

13:30.157 --> 13:33.247
♪ And hear you make a sound

13:33.290 --> 13:37.077
It's not as good as mine,
but let's party.

13:37.120 --> 13:38.861
Cheers, everyone. Salud.Cheers.

13:38.905 --> 13:40.341
Come on.

13:40.384 --> 13:41.864
And over here.

13:41.908 --> 13:44.824
So, uh, what's customary now?Get more seats or...

13:44.867 --> 13:46.651
Yes. Let's do that.
Okay.

13:46.695 --> 13:50.133
[Indistinct conversations, musiccontinues]

13:50.177 --> 13:57.097
♪

13:57.140 --> 13:58.881
I'm freezing.
Are you freezing?

13:58.925 --> 14:01.144
Oh!
You did a lot.

14:01.188 --> 14:02.842
Here.

14:02.885 --> 14:04.582
Okay.

14:04.626 --> 14:08.412
♪

14:08.456 --> 14:09.892
The game's truth or dare.

14:09.936 --> 14:11.938
Iris: I'm in.Hope: Cool.

14:11.981 --> 14:15.289
I don't know what that is,but yeah, let's play it.

14:15.332 --> 14:16.899
It's simple --
All you got to do

14:16.943 --> 14:18.466
is you got to pick one
or the other.

14:18.509 --> 14:20.163
Iris, truth or dare?

14:20.207 --> 14:23.079
[Chuckles]
Uh, truth.

14:23.123 --> 14:25.429
Oh, I'm good. Thank you.Percy: Truth.

14:25.473 --> 14:26.953
If you could do
whatever you wanted right now,

14:26.996 --> 14:29.346
anything at all,
what would you do?

14:29.390 --> 14:30.347
Easy.

14:30.391 --> 14:31.566
I'd hit the Louvre...

14:31.609 --> 14:33.133
Mm.
...see some good art.

14:33.176 --> 14:35.918
I mean --
Oh, Eugène Delacroix's, um...

14:35.962 --> 14:37.964
"Liberty Leading the People."[Snores]

14:38.007 --> 14:40.053
Oh!
The brushstrokes.

14:40.096 --> 14:42.533
The actual canvas!

14:42.577 --> 14:44.405
Oh.

14:44.448 --> 14:47.625
I was hoping for an answer withless of a tranquilizing effect.

14:47.669 --> 14:49.236
[Laughing]
Bullshit!

14:49.279 --> 14:52.021
It's got the best art
in the world.

14:52.065 --> 14:53.936
Granted, it's probably not even
standing,

14:53.980 --> 14:56.939
and even if it were, I'd doubt
I'd ever get to see it.

14:56.983 --> 15:00.856
But...a girl can dream,
right?

15:01.726 --> 15:03.685
Fair enough.

15:03.728 --> 15:07.950
Here's to dreaming
and, uh...never saying "never."

15:07.994 --> 15:13.390
♪ Never been before

15:13.434 --> 15:15.044
Tony:
[Laughs]

15:15.088 --> 15:17.655
[Music playing in distance]

15:19.440 --> 15:22.225
Leo and Will --
They sound like good people.

15:22.269 --> 15:24.793
Yes, they are.

15:25.707 --> 15:28.405
I mean, the thing is...
I don't even know

15:28.449 --> 15:31.626
if what we're doing
is gonna wind up helping them

15:31.669 --> 15:34.629
or just putting them
in more danger.

15:34.672 --> 15:36.544
Well, if there's one thingI've learned, kiddo,

15:36.587 --> 15:38.241
it's that you can't predictthe future.

15:38.285 --> 15:39.590
Mm.

15:39.634 --> 15:44.204
I was a man of many vicesbefore all this.

15:44.247 --> 15:45.640
Oh, yeah?

15:45.683 --> 15:48.121
Playing chicken
with rock bottom.

15:48.164 --> 15:50.819
Didn't even know who Percy wastill my sister --

15:50.862 --> 15:54.997
his -- his mother --split from her husband...

15:55.041 --> 15:58.044
and the court appointed mehis legal guardian.

15:58.087 --> 16:00.089
It was like my prayershad been answered.

16:00.133 --> 16:02.004
All that free money
from the state?

16:02.048 --> 16:03.875
I hit pay dirt
with that kid.

16:03.919 --> 16:06.008
Hm.

16:06.052 --> 16:10.839
Thing was...he wasn't with memore than a day

16:10.882 --> 16:13.581
before I knew I'd give my lifefor his.

16:15.757 --> 16:17.846
Family.

16:17.889 --> 16:20.240
It's a thing.
Who knew?

16:22.198 --> 16:25.071
[Laughter in distance]

16:25.114 --> 16:27.464
Yeah.

16:27.508 --> 16:30.641
Who knew, huh?

16:30.685 --> 16:35.081
♪

16:35.124 --> 16:36.343
Truth. Oh, my God.
Oh!

16:36.386 --> 16:38.345
Elton:
Right. In that case,

16:38.388 --> 16:40.651
I have a four-part question
that tiers off --

16:40.695 --> 16:43.741
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Sorry, Elton.
Gonna have to keep this simple.

16:43.785 --> 16:46.092
What's the worst thing
you ever done?

16:46.135 --> 16:51.619
♪

16:51.662 --> 16:53.795
[Exhales sharply]
What kind of question is that?

16:53.838 --> 16:55.536
I mean,
it's not even your turn.

16:55.579 --> 16:57.233
You afraid to answerthe question?

16:57.277 --> 16:59.018
Come on.

16:59.061 --> 17:00.671
What's the worst thingyou ever done?

17:00.715 --> 17:03.544
♪

17:03.587 --> 17:05.502
Fine.

17:05.546 --> 17:08.462
Back at the U, I locked
the school faculty bathroom

17:08.505 --> 17:11.726
and spiked the teachers'
coffee maker with laxatives.

17:11.769 --> 17:15.686
Precious, precious laxatives.[Laughter]

17:15.730 --> 17:16.948
She did.

17:16.992 --> 17:17.906
Elton:
[Laughs]

17:17.949 --> 17:19.299
Next.

17:19.342 --> 17:21.779
Come on.
I said the truth.

17:21.823 --> 17:23.433
That <i>is</i>the truth.

17:23.477 --> 17:25.479
Ah.

17:25.522 --> 17:27.263
You think you can cona con man?

17:27.307 --> 17:29.352
[Exhales deeply]

17:29.396 --> 17:31.702
I know you're hiding something.Come on. Spill it.

17:31.746 --> 17:33.226
What's the worst thingyou ever done?

17:33.269 --> 17:34.792
She -- She already told you.
It's the laxative thing.

17:34.836 --> 17:36.185
Sorry.No, I don't think it is.

17:36.229 --> 17:38.361
Stop!

17:38.405 --> 17:40.407
Stop it.
Leave her alone.

17:40.450 --> 17:42.365
Silas, it's okay.

17:42.409 --> 17:46.500
Percy's right.
There is something else.

17:46.543 --> 17:49.155
The worst thing
that I've ever done...

17:51.505 --> 17:54.682
...is agree to play
this stupid game.

17:54.725 --> 17:55.683
Hope.

17:55.726 --> 17:56.727
No. No.
Allow me.

17:56.771 --> 17:58.294
Hope.[Clears throat] Hope.

17:58.338 --> 18:00.253
I was just playing around.

18:00.296 --> 18:01.689
Yeah.
She knows.

18:04.822 --> 18:06.520
Hope.
Hope, wait up. Hope...

18:06.563 --> 18:08.609
What?
What is it?

18:08.652 --> 18:10.698
Nothing. Everything.
Look. Okay.

18:10.741 --> 18:12.917
It -- It <i>is</i>a stupid game,
all right?

18:12.961 --> 18:16.356
And I was just playing
'cause I-I...

18:16.399 --> 18:18.749
[Sighs]
Just...

18:18.793 --> 18:23.885
Um...thanks, Elton.

18:23.928 --> 18:26.322
But, uh...

18:26.366 --> 18:28.585
I think you're drunk,all right?

18:28.629 --> 18:32.111
And I need to be alone.

18:32.154 --> 18:34.200
[Footsteps echoing]

18:38.465 --> 18:40.206
Okay.

18:42.860 --> 18:46.125
[Down-tempo music plays]

18:46.168 --> 18:53.871
♪

18:53.915 --> 18:56.178
Wilkins: Containing the crisis
is the strategy,

18:56.222 --> 18:58.180
separating the well
from the sick.

18:58.224 --> 18:59.573
The source and nature
of the current crisis

18:59.616 --> 19:01.183
cannot be confirmed.

19:01.227 --> 19:03.359
But with reports of widespread
rioting and violence,

19:03.403 --> 19:06.406
you are being deployed
into the city's service tunnels

19:06.449 --> 19:09.887
to locate civilians
and escort them to safety.

19:09.931 --> 19:12.281
If you are under threat
of any kind,

19:12.325 --> 19:15.371
you are to eliminate
any and all hostile targets

19:15.415 --> 19:16.938
that you encounter.

19:16.981 --> 19:18.200
Kill!

19:18.244 --> 19:19.941
Kill!Kill!Kill!
Kill!

19:19.984 --> 19:22.248
[Down-tempo music plays]

19:31.213 --> 19:34.042
I heard it came back
on a rocket,

19:34.085 --> 19:35.783
that it started in space.

19:35.826 --> 19:38.220
You know,
somebody breathed it in,

19:38.264 --> 19:40.918
it turned their stomachs,
and then they got on a plane --

19:40.962 --> 19:42.268
Shut up, Owens.

19:42.311 --> 19:43.660
[Door opens]

19:43.704 --> 19:45.488
Man:
Come on. This way. Let's go.

19:45.532 --> 19:47.795
Multiple targets ahead.[Walker growling]

19:47.838 --> 19:50.145
Drake:Hold fire. Hold fire.

19:51.842 --> 19:54.062
[Walkers growling,
gunshots echoing]

19:54.105 --> 19:56.282
[Bullets ricocheting,
casings clattering]

19:56.325 --> 19:59.241
[Walker hissing]

19:59.285 --> 20:01.156
[Gunshots]

20:01.200 --> 20:04.159
[Casings clattering]

20:04.203 --> 20:06.509
Simms: What the hell, man?What were those things?

20:06.553 --> 20:10.165
They <i>were</i>people.
Sure as hell ain't now.

20:10.209 --> 20:12.167
You see more,
go for the heads.

20:12.211 --> 20:13.603
That did it.

20:13.647 --> 20:17.216
[Screaming in distance]

20:17.259 --> 20:21.176
We got civilian friendlies aliveup there.

20:21.220 --> 20:22.525
That's our mission.

20:22.569 --> 20:30.185
♪

20:30.229 --> 20:33.667
[Walker growling,
indistinct screaming]

20:33.710 --> 20:36.278
[Rumbling, lights click]

20:36.322 --> 20:37.758
Drake:
Damn it.

20:39.629 --> 20:42.110
[Click, night-vision whirring]

20:43.329 --> 20:45.374
Lance Corporal Mallick,what are you seeing?

20:45.418 --> 20:46.375
Talk to me.

20:46.419 --> 20:48.377
A lot of activity ahead.

20:48.421 --> 20:50.336
Stay close.

20:50.379 --> 20:51.902
[Walkers growling]

20:51.946 --> 20:54.383
Woman: Come this way![Child screams]

20:54.427 --> 20:57.952
Lance Corporal Mallick,as your designated spotter,

20:57.995 --> 21:00.128
I strongly suggestwe start shooting something.

21:00.171 --> 21:03.174
Can't tell the friendlies
from the hostiles.

21:03.218 --> 21:05.176
[Crowd screaming]Try thermal.

21:05.220 --> 21:06.352
[Night-vision whirring]

21:06.395 --> 21:08.745
Hostiles have
a lower body temp.

21:08.789 --> 21:10.704
Let's move!

21:10.747 --> 21:12.880
[Gunshots, crowd screaming]

21:12.923 --> 21:15.361
[Walkers growling]

21:18.364 --> 21:20.061
Move it!

21:20.104 --> 21:21.454
[Gunshot, walker hisses]

21:21.497 --> 21:23.412
Man:
Come on!

21:23.456 --> 21:25.501
[Dramatic music plays]

21:25.545 --> 21:28.722
♪

21:28.765 --> 21:31.725
[Indistinct conversations,
whispering]

21:32.987 --> 21:36.556
It's okay.
You're safe.

21:39.080 --> 21:41.300
We're getting you
out of here.

21:42.823 --> 21:44.651
[Door opens]

21:44.694 --> 21:46.740
[Insects chirping]

21:52.049 --> 21:54.400
Huck:You shouldn't be up here drunk.

21:56.097 --> 21:57.620
You shouldn't be up here
at all.

21:57.664 --> 21:59.579
What are you doing here?

21:59.622 --> 22:01.755
Never mind me.

22:02.843 --> 22:05.715
You want to tell mewhat's been eating at you?

22:05.759 --> 22:08.327
Something's been up
since The Blaze.

22:10.764 --> 22:13.549
And it ain't something small.
That's for sure.

22:20.513 --> 22:23.385
Tell me.
What's up?

22:31.393 --> 22:34.048
[Voice breaking]
I killed someone.

22:34.091 --> 22:37.573
It was the night
the sky fell.

22:37.617 --> 22:40.271
I didn't know
who she was.

22:42.796 --> 22:46.365
She was scared my momwas gonna take her truck.

22:47.714 --> 22:49.803
She freaked out and...

22:49.846 --> 22:51.457
[Sobs]

22:51.500 --> 22:54.416
...she shot my mom.

22:54.460 --> 22:55.809
[Sniffs]

22:55.852 --> 22:57.854
She dropped the gun,and I picked it up,

22:57.898 --> 22:59.900
and I pointed it at her.

22:59.943 --> 23:01.423
And it went off.

23:01.467 --> 23:04.818
She was pregnant,
and I killed her.

23:05.862 --> 23:08.343
She was Elton's mom.

23:09.910 --> 23:12.608
[Sobs]

23:12.652 --> 23:14.044
You were just a kid.

23:14.088 --> 23:15.872
But I did it!

23:15.916 --> 23:19.136
You were a kid, and she killed
your mom in front of you.

23:19.180 --> 23:22.662
[Sniffs]
Elton doesn't know.

23:22.705 --> 23:26.187
Iris knows,but not that it's Elton's mom.

23:26.230 --> 23:28.319
And they shouldn't.

23:29.538 --> 23:32.889
We can't change
the things we've done.

23:32.933 --> 23:35.414
Just find the strength
to carry the truth

23:35.457 --> 23:38.025
for everybody else
so they don't have to.

23:38.068 --> 23:39.896
But how?
[Sobs]

23:39.940 --> 23:42.595
[Down-tempo music plays]

23:42.638 --> 23:45.641
Welcome to the party, kid.

23:45.685 --> 23:48.078
[Exhales deeply]

23:48.122 --> 23:51.386
Some nights,
it's so damn dark.

23:53.301 --> 23:56.435
And then they still manage
to get darker.

23:58.654 --> 24:02.789
But the light...will come.

24:02.832 --> 24:04.921
I promise you.

24:04.965 --> 24:06.923
It'll come.

24:15.497 --> 24:23.984
♪

24:24.027 --> 24:25.768
Tony: In there somewhere
is a whole stash

24:25.812 --> 24:29.642
of refined CRM fuel
just ripe for the taking.

24:29.685 --> 24:31.513
Big place.

24:31.557 --> 24:34.168
We'll split up, start at
the bottom, work our way up.

24:34.211 --> 24:35.952
And these places are clearof empties, yeah?

24:35.996 --> 24:37.780
As far as we can tell.

24:37.824 --> 24:41.044
CRM keeps their shit locked up
pretty tight.

24:41.088 --> 24:43.394
Good thing lock-picking's
our thing.

24:43.438 --> 24:45.222
Mine too.

24:45.266 --> 24:47.486
Still, we should stay alert.

24:47.529 --> 24:49.313
♪

24:49.357 --> 24:52.534
Hope, we're heading out.You and me. Come on.

24:52.578 --> 24:54.493
[Water dripping]

24:54.536 --> 24:57.321
♪

24:57.365 --> 25:00.716
So...still gonna to talk to him,huh?

25:00.760 --> 25:04.198
I know what you're gonna say,
but I finished his mom's book.

25:04.241 --> 25:06.940
She was smart and kind
and...

25:06.983 --> 25:11.379
I think she just got scared
and did a bad thing, all right?

25:11.422 --> 25:13.381
If I can forgive her,
then maybe Elton can forgive --

25:13.424 --> 25:16.732
Is this about him
or this about you?

25:18.038 --> 25:19.953
Truth's a funny thing.

25:19.996 --> 25:22.738
People say that'swhat they want, but it isn't.

25:22.782 --> 25:25.915
What? So we're just stuck
living a lie?

25:27.003 --> 25:28.962
That's the thing.

25:29.005 --> 25:33.183
If they don't know it's a lie,they get to just live.

25:33.227 --> 25:37.710
We pay the cost, but theyget to live 'cause of us.

25:37.753 --> 25:39.973
[Water dripping]

25:46.893 --> 25:49.809
Owens?
Where the hell are the others?

25:49.852 --> 25:53.029
[Indistinct conversations, fencerattling]

25:53.073 --> 25:54.901
Wilkins:
Listen up.

25:54.944 --> 25:56.946
[Indistinct talking on radio]

25:56.990 --> 25:59.601
We received orders,
per Central Command.

25:59.645 --> 26:01.734
Sunset Protocols are in effect.

26:01.777 --> 26:04.867
Pending final authorization,
all units in the hot zone

26:04.911 --> 26:07.783
will be directed to kill
all targets in their grid.

26:07.827 --> 26:12.353
With respect, sir, what the hellare you talking about?

26:12.396 --> 26:14.703
That means you put down anythingstill walking --

26:14.747 --> 26:18.968
friendly or unfriendly,civilian or hostile,

26:19.012 --> 26:20.927
living or dead.

26:20.970 --> 26:23.538
[Down-tempo music plays]

26:23.582 --> 26:25.409
[Clatter, metal scraping]Hope?

26:25.453 --> 26:29.457
♪

26:29.500 --> 26:31.328
Hope?

26:32.112 --> 26:33.722
Talk to me.

26:33.766 --> 26:35.245
[Water dripping]

27:06.102 --> 27:13.849
♪

27:13.893 --> 27:15.634
Drop the gun.

27:15.677 --> 27:18.158
Do it -- now.

27:19.072 --> 27:21.378
[Sobs, whimpers]

27:21.422 --> 27:30.866
♪

27:30.910 --> 27:33.695
Easy, man.
Easy.

27:33.739 --> 27:35.784
Not one more step!
[Sobs]

27:35.828 --> 27:39.353
♪

27:44.401 --> 27:46.926
So, when you and Percy get usto where we're going,

27:46.969 --> 27:48.710
what's next for you?

27:48.754 --> 27:50.712
More of the same, I suppose.

27:50.756 --> 27:52.192
What's that?

27:52.235 --> 27:55.848
Just keep on moving,keep conning?

27:55.891 --> 27:56.979
Keep surviving.

27:57.023 --> 27:59.329
It's what we do.I hear that.

27:59.373 --> 28:00.722
Percy had to grow up fastout here.

28:00.766 --> 28:02.463
He doesn't know
any other way.

28:02.506 --> 28:05.596
You know, he reminds me a lot
of me when I was his age.

28:05.640 --> 28:10.036
Living on the streets.
Survival was everything.

28:10.079 --> 28:15.911
I met the girls' dad, Leo,
and then he showed me...

28:15.955 --> 28:18.958
showed me there was more.

28:19.001 --> 28:21.525
Showed me I could be more.

28:21.569 --> 28:23.136
That was another time.

28:23.179 --> 28:25.529
Things are different now.

28:25.573 --> 28:28.576
Maybe it doesn't
have to be.

28:28.619 --> 28:30.317
You smell that?

28:31.622 --> 28:34.713
They took the timeto stash this supply good.

28:34.756 --> 28:36.453
[Down-tempo music plays]

28:36.497 --> 28:38.107
[Metal squeaking]

28:38.151 --> 28:42.198
♪

28:42.242 --> 28:44.635
[Sniffs]

28:44.679 --> 28:45.941
Jackpot.

28:45.985 --> 28:48.248
[Chuckles]

28:48.291 --> 28:49.771
Cabinet looks new.

28:49.815 --> 28:52.469
Oh.

28:52.513 --> 28:53.993
♪

28:54.036 --> 28:56.169
I said stay the hell back![Sobbing]

28:57.300 --> 28:59.476
I'm a statue.

29:01.914 --> 29:05.178
You good, pal?

29:05.221 --> 29:06.875
What happened to your leg?

29:06.919 --> 29:10.096
No. I'm gonna askthe questions, okay?

29:10.139 --> 29:14.100
You're them --with the helicopters.

29:14.143 --> 29:15.449
How many more?

29:16.885 --> 29:18.931
Just me and the girl.

29:18.974 --> 29:22.021
We're not them.
We're just scavenging.

29:22.064 --> 29:23.500
Got lucky.You're lying!

29:23.544 --> 29:25.024
You both got the symbolon your jacket.

29:25.067 --> 29:26.416
What happened?

29:26.460 --> 29:28.157
One of the dead take a bite
out of you?

29:28.201 --> 29:30.594
Shut the hell up![Gasps, sobs]

29:30.638 --> 29:33.336
[Breathing heavily]
You <i>are</i>them.

29:33.380 --> 29:35.208
This place --
This place is ours.

29:35.251 --> 29:36.992
You just came in
and took it.

29:37.036 --> 29:38.124
We took it back.

29:38.167 --> 29:41.344
We didn't take anything.

29:41.388 --> 29:43.651
I'm not them.

29:43.694 --> 29:46.872
You don't look too good.

29:46.915 --> 29:49.048
Come on.
Let's talk about it.

29:50.310 --> 29:52.747
I don't know.

29:52.791 --> 29:56.403
I j-- I just woke up,and my brother, he'd...

29:56.446 --> 29:57.796
he'd turned.

29:57.839 --> 30:01.451
I stabbed him.He's dead in the next room.

30:01.495 --> 30:04.324
Well, you ain't gonna last
much longer with that leg.

30:04.367 --> 30:06.456
You know that, right?

30:06.500 --> 30:09.982
♪

30:10.025 --> 30:13.333
Stop! I will shoot her!I swear to God!

30:13.376 --> 30:14.813
[Sobs]

30:14.856 --> 30:18.120
Her name's Hope.
They call me Huck.

30:18.164 --> 30:20.949
We're just passing through.

30:20.993 --> 30:22.081
What's your name?

30:22.124 --> 30:25.345
[Breathing heavily]

30:25.388 --> 30:26.563
Walter.

30:26.607 --> 30:28.217
Listen, Walter.

30:28.261 --> 30:31.960
I can help you, but first
you got to let my friend go.

30:32.004 --> 30:33.570
No.

30:33.614 --> 30:35.485
You didn't let me finish.

30:35.529 --> 30:37.052
Then you train your sights
on me.

30:37.096 --> 30:38.358
Huck, no!

30:38.401 --> 30:43.058
Walter, she's just a kid --
harmless.

30:43.102 --> 30:45.408
Focus on me, all right?

30:45.452 --> 30:49.195
♪

30:49.238 --> 30:51.153
[Grunts, sobs]

30:51.197 --> 30:52.415
♪

30:52.459 --> 30:54.461
Okay.

30:54.504 --> 30:56.942
Now let's talk about
how we're gonna save you.

30:56.985 --> 30:58.030
That's impossible.

30:58.073 --> 31:02.208
We can do it.
Trust me.

31:02.251 --> 31:03.731
Stand by.

31:03.774 --> 31:06.255
[Baby crying]

31:06.299 --> 31:07.866
Huck:
We can't do this.

31:07.909 --> 31:09.302
An order from Central Commandis like an order from God!

31:09.345 --> 31:10.607
We have to!

31:10.651 --> 31:12.783
What if those peopleare infected, huh?

31:12.827 --> 31:14.873
What if shooting them
is the only way

31:14.916 --> 31:16.787
to stop this thing
from spreading?

31:16.831 --> 31:19.790
We're gonna have to take that
leg before it spreads further.

31:19.834 --> 31:21.183
No way.

31:21.227 --> 31:22.532
It's been too long.

31:22.576 --> 31:25.405
You shouldn't be here.

31:25.448 --> 31:27.973
Maybe none of us
should be.

31:28.016 --> 31:29.626
I'm sorry. It's not personal.I just --

31:29.670 --> 31:34.196
You shoot me, you take your lifewith that bullet, too.

31:34.240 --> 31:38.200
You...You can help me?

31:38.244 --> 31:40.072
I've seen people
survive amputations

31:40.115 --> 31:41.638
hours after infection.

31:41.682 --> 31:42.944
You're lying.

31:42.988 --> 31:44.598
I'm not.Wilkins: Listen up.

31:44.641 --> 31:47.340
I just received
final authentication

31:47.383 --> 31:49.255
of Sunset Protocols.

31:49.298 --> 31:51.953
Y'all know me.

31:51.997 --> 31:54.129
I don't like this
any more than you do.

31:54.173 --> 31:56.305
We are being trusted
with these orders

31:56.349 --> 31:58.568
because they are
absolutely necessary.

31:58.612 --> 32:01.397
Any Marine, including myself,

32:01.441 --> 32:03.269
who fails to follow
these orders

32:03.312 --> 32:07.229
will be taken into custody
and brought up on charges.

32:07.273 --> 32:08.970
Jennifer...

32:09.014 --> 32:11.973
[Baby crying]

32:12.017 --> 32:14.454
...we don't have a choice.

32:14.497 --> 32:16.673
[Down-tempo music plays]

32:16.717 --> 32:19.285
Huck:
Gun's getting heavy, huh?

32:19.328 --> 32:21.548
It's all good.

32:21.591 --> 32:23.854
Nobody would blame you
for dropping it.

32:23.898 --> 32:25.682
♪

32:25.726 --> 32:27.684
I-I just...

32:27.728 --> 32:30.122
It wasn't supposed to gothis way.

32:30.165 --> 32:32.689
[Grunts, sobs]

32:32.733 --> 32:34.430
♪

32:34.474 --> 32:38.043
[Whispering] It's okay.It's okay.

32:38.086 --> 32:40.175
Shh.

32:40.219 --> 32:42.090
You can save me?

32:42.134 --> 32:43.526
[Breathing heavily]

32:43.570 --> 32:45.615
Yeah.

32:45.659 --> 32:46.965
I can save you.

32:47.008 --> 32:49.619
♪

32:49.663 --> 32:50.664
Marines!

32:50.707 --> 32:52.405
[Crowd shouting]

32:52.448 --> 32:55.016
On my command!

32:55.060 --> 32:58.237
[Crowd shouting, baby crying]

32:58.280 --> 33:04.591
♪

33:04.634 --> 33:06.549
[Click, night-vision whirring,
gunshots echoing]

33:06.593 --> 33:07.942
Wilkins:
[Grunts]

33:07.986 --> 33:10.379
Drake:
Jennifer! Jennifer, stop!

33:10.423 --> 33:12.294
Jennifer, stop!

33:12.338 --> 33:13.730
[Casings clattering]

33:13.774 --> 33:15.123
Put it down.

33:15.167 --> 33:17.647
No.
I'm a Marine.

33:17.691 --> 33:19.606
I don't know what the hell
you are.

33:19.649 --> 33:21.042
[Baby crying]

33:21.086 --> 33:23.566
[Gun cocks, gunshot echoes]

33:23.610 --> 33:30.443
♪

33:30.486 --> 33:32.358
Hope:
You said you could save him.

33:33.446 --> 33:36.101
Huck:Time to forgive yourself, kid.

33:36.144 --> 33:39.017
You got a future.You got to see that now.

33:39.060 --> 33:42.150
♪

33:42.194 --> 33:44.848
Iris:What the hell happened?

33:44.892 --> 33:46.720
Are you okay?

33:46.763 --> 33:49.766
H-Huck -- Huck saved me.

33:50.680 --> 33:51.812
Jesus, Huck.

33:51.855 --> 33:54.641
It's okay.
We're okay.

33:54.684 --> 33:56.469
This guy had walkies,
supplies.

33:56.512 --> 33:59.602
We found the fuel.

33:59.646 --> 34:01.474
Let's get the hell out
of here.

34:01.517 --> 34:06.609
We found something else, too...
locked in the cabinet.

34:06.653 --> 34:08.655
What are those?

34:08.698 --> 34:13.312
Potentially...
something to work with.

34:17.011 --> 34:20.145
[Birds chirping]

34:32.070 --> 34:34.811
You think these are encryptedCRM lunch orders?

34:34.855 --> 34:36.639
[Chuckles]

34:36.683 --> 34:38.337
If we could
just crack this,

34:38.380 --> 34:40.991
it could tell us more
about them,

34:41.035 --> 34:44.343
help our chances of saving Dad
when we get to him.

34:45.300 --> 34:46.910
Maybe.

34:46.954 --> 34:49.261
Yeah.

34:49.304 --> 34:51.350
Maybe.

34:57.443 --> 35:00.185
Hope, it feels like
we're changing.

35:02.839 --> 35:05.625
It feels like it's
just the start.

35:07.801 --> 35:10.064
Hey, Silas.
Hold on.

35:10.108 --> 35:12.632
Tony has something
he wants to say.

35:16.201 --> 35:17.550
Tony:
Okay.

35:17.593 --> 35:20.553
So, after talking it over
with Felix,

35:20.596 --> 35:23.382
Percy and I
have decided to...

35:23.425 --> 35:26.646
extend the terms
of our agreement with you.

35:26.689 --> 35:28.430
Yeah, insteadof dropping you guys off,

35:28.474 --> 35:29.866
we want to stick around,

35:29.910 --> 35:32.478
do what we canto help you guys find your dad.

35:32.521 --> 35:34.610
After that, who knows?

35:34.654 --> 35:36.264
Let the chips fall
where they may.

35:36.308 --> 35:38.092
Felix: All right.
Let's all get some sleep.

35:38.136 --> 35:40.573
We're hitting the road
at first light.

35:40.616 --> 35:42.270
Sounds good.

35:42.314 --> 35:45.099
I'll go charge up the walkies
and top off the tank.

35:48.146 --> 35:49.495
Hey.

35:49.538 --> 35:51.671
So, uh...

35:53.281 --> 35:57.633
...would you maybe want to
see me by the truck in an hour?

35:57.677 --> 35:58.808
Why?What's at the truck?

35:58.852 --> 36:00.201
Just me.

36:00.245 --> 36:02.551
Just, uh...
need to get my gloves back.

36:02.595 --> 36:04.814
Oh.I can give them to you now.

36:04.858 --> 36:06.076
Uh, no, no.

36:06.120 --> 36:10.559
Uh, my hands...
aren't cold now.

36:10.603 --> 36:15.782
Uh...but they will be
in about an hour?

36:17.262 --> 36:18.915
An hour.
Okay.

36:18.959 --> 36:20.961
Yeah.

36:21.004 --> 36:23.137
[Chuckles]

36:33.713 --> 36:35.410
Um, hey.

36:35.454 --> 36:38.196
Um, I-I didn't get a chance
to tell you this earlier,

36:38.239 --> 36:42.025
but, um...I-I'm sorry
for what happened to you.

36:42.069 --> 36:43.636
[Door opens, closes]

36:43.679 --> 36:45.594
I-It means everything to me
that you're still alive

36:45.638 --> 36:48.380
and here with us.Thanks, but...

36:48.423 --> 36:50.251
I mean...
[Clears throat]

36:50.295 --> 36:52.906
I wouldn't want to lose you
like the, um...

36:54.386 --> 36:56.866
[Chuckles]...queen of hearts.

36:56.910 --> 36:59.304
[Down-tempo music plays]

36:59.347 --> 37:01.349
I know
it's just a stupid trick,

37:01.393 --> 37:04.265
but show somebody
the impossible,

37:04.309 --> 37:08.400
and suddenly everything
seems possible.

37:08.443 --> 37:14.623
I just wanted to thank you...for sharing this with me.

37:14.667 --> 37:17.235
Your mother seems like she wasan amazing woman.

37:17.278 --> 37:19.237
She was.

37:20.281 --> 37:23.502
And hey,
maybe she still is.

37:23.545 --> 37:25.765
I mean, who knows, right?

37:25.808 --> 37:28.246
Everything is possible.

37:28.289 --> 37:31.553
Yeah.Everything is possible.

38:03.629 --> 38:12.246
♪

38:12.290 --> 38:14.944
[Insects chirping]

38:14.988 --> 38:17.251
[Footsteps approaching]

38:18.383 --> 38:21.603
You were right.

38:21.647 --> 38:25.303
Telling Elton...
[Exhales deeply]

38:25.346 --> 38:27.740
I'd just be doing it for me,not for him.

38:27.783 --> 38:31.396
The truthwould just crush him.

38:31.439 --> 38:33.136
You're a good person, Hope.

38:33.180 --> 38:35.138
[Down-tempo music plays]

38:35.182 --> 38:38.881
♪

38:38.925 --> 38:43.364
I took this from Elton's momafter I...

38:44.670 --> 38:46.672
I stole it.

38:47.673 --> 38:49.588
Still think
I'm a good person?

38:50.980 --> 38:54.419
I know you are.
The necklace proves it.

38:54.462 --> 38:58.031
♪

38:58.074 --> 39:00.773
You took it
as a reminder...

39:02.601 --> 39:04.690
...something you wear
every day

39:04.733 --> 39:07.432
to remember the bad
you've done...

39:09.347 --> 39:14.439
...a reminder to keep living
to do good,

39:14.482 --> 39:18.138
'cause that's the only way
to make the bad mean something.

39:18.181 --> 39:20.358
♪

39:20.401 --> 39:23.186
You're gonna be okay, Hope.

39:28.801 --> 39:34.284
♪

39:34.328 --> 39:35.721
[Insects chirping]

39:35.764 --> 39:37.244
Percy?

39:40.465 --> 39:42.858
[Down-tempo music plays]

40:15.848 --> 40:24.030
♪

40:24.073 --> 40:26.598
[Glass breaking in distance]

40:26.641 --> 40:29.688
[Footsteps departing]

40:55.191 --> 40:57.716
Percy?

40:57.759 --> 41:00.240
[Hinges squeaking]

41:00.283 --> 41:01.807
Percy?

41:06.159 --> 41:07.334
[Dramatic music plays]

41:07.377 --> 41:08.901
Tony?

41:08.944 --> 41:12.208
♪

41:12.252 --> 41:14.602
Hope?
Felix?

41:14.646 --> 41:17.126
Somebody, help!

41:17.170 --> 41:26.266
♪

41:26.309 --> 41:27.397
Percy.

41:27.441 --> 41:28.573
Felix:
Iris?!

41:28.616 --> 41:30.662
[Breathing heavily]

41:30.705 --> 41:32.707
Holy shit.

41:32.751 --> 41:35.275
Hope:
That's Silas's.

41:35.318 --> 41:37.930
What the hell?

41:37.973 --> 41:41.324
♪

41:41.368 --> 41:43.283
Oh, my God.

41:43.326 --> 41:45.285
Cover me.

41:45.328 --> 41:48.462
Who's in there?
Who did this?

41:48.506 --> 42:00.561
♪

42:00.605 --> 42:02.389
[Hinges squeaking]

42:02.432 --> 42:03.782
Felix:
Silas?

42:03.825 --> 42:07.568
♪

42:07.612 --> 42:09.614
Silas.

42:09.657 --> 42:13.226
♪
